[Student "S"]
{With 11 points and a beautiful 6-card suit this is the perfect hand for a Weak-2 opener. So you open 2\D. Partner responds 2NT. 

Partner's 2NT bid is a standard response to a Weak 2-bid. You are expected to rebid your suit if you have a minimum (6-8 point) hand. Otherwise you are to bid an outside suit in which you hold a high card - this is called "showing a feature". And the final possibility is this one, where you have a solid suit,  either A K Q x x x or A K J 10 x x. In this case you bid 3NT.

South would play 3NT.

Click 

North plays 3NT. East leads \SJ. West plays \SK.

<b>North plays 3NT. East leads \SJ. West plays \SK.</b>

Winner count: \S 2 : \H 1 : \D 3 : \C 1 : Total = 7

The \S lead assures you of two tricks in the suit. So you only need to create two more. If the \Ds split 3-2 (likely) you could get 3 extra tricks there. But there's a danger - if they split 4-1 you wouldn't have an entry to them. Well, you wouldn't have an entry unless you <b>DUCKED</b> the first \D. Then a 4-1 split wouldn't prevent you from making 5 \D winners.

So you win the \SA and lead the \D3, planning to duck. 

<b>East shows out</b>.

Make <b>PLAN B</b>, then  

So you win the \SA and lead the \D3, planning to duck. 

<b>East shows out</b>.

That's tough. No matter how you play them you can only get 3 \D winners. So you must turn elsewhere - elsewhere being the \C suit.

Win the \DQ but don't play another \D yet, you need an entry back to dummy later. Instead, lead the \C2 and finesse your \CT. East will win with one of the high \Cs and probably return a \S. You may as well take the \SQ now. Play your \D8 to dummy's \DK, cash the \DA, then play the \C4, finessing your \CJ. Fortunately this wins and when you cash your \CA both defenders follow. The rest of your clubs are good and you make an overtrick.

Sometimes you have to change your plan.

When the \Ds turned out to be 5-0 you had to get lucky. Your back-up Plan wasn't likely to work - it required the missing \C honors to be split, but also required a 3-3 \C split, not a likely outcome.

But there was no other choice so you have to try it. }
[Play "W"]SJ

